</i><sub class=\"lower-index\">1</sub><sup class=\"upper-index\">2</sup> - <i>a</i><sub class=\"lower-index\">3</sub><sup class=\"upper-index\">2</sup> - <i>a</i><sub class=\"lower-index\">5</sub><sup class=\"upper-index\">2 </sup></div>\n<div dir=\"ltr\">if we considered that the length of one small triangle equal to 1 and consider the big triangle have sides of X cm then we have area</div>","fields":{"slug":"/blog/posts/whats-the-number-of-triangles-in-irregular-hexagon/"},"frontmatter":{"date":"July 21, 2017","title":"What's the number of Triangles in irregular hexagon ?","toArabic":null},"timeToRead":1,"wordCount":{"words":null}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/blog/posts/whats-the-number-of-triangles-in-irregular-hexagon/","toArabic":null}}}